<m:mover>
<m:mi>X</m:mi>
<m:mo>¯</m:mo>
</m:mover>
</m:mrow>
</m:math>
</li>
</ul>

<section>
<title>Comments</title>
<body>
<ol>
<li>Note that since the formula for the intercept <em>a</em> depends on the value of the slope, <em>b</em>, you need to find <em>b</em> first.</li>
<li>The slope of the least squares regression line can be interpreted as the average change in the response variable when the explanatory variable increases by 1 unit.</li>
</ol>
</body>
</section>
